Durban - Reaction Units South Africa (Rusa) reported that a 28-year-old man was allegedly stabbed to death by his “friend” during an argument at a residence in Cottonlands, Verulam last week. Rusa Spokesperson Prem Balram said reaction officers arrived at the scene just after 1am on Friday morning. Balram said members located the victim lying in a pool of blood in a house. He said the man sustained stab wounds to his abdomen and chest which resulted in his death. “It was established that the suspect and the deceased were consuming alcohol with friends throughout yesterday (Thursday). The two began arguing for unconfirmed reasons when his drinking buddy stabbed him,” said Balram. Balram said the attacker then fled the scene. Provincial police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Nqobile Gwala, said a case of murder is being investigated by Verulam SAPS. “It is alleged that on 8 July 2022 at Cottonlands in Verulam, a 28-year-old man was stabbed by a known suspect following an argument. The victim sustained stab wounds on the chest and abdomen. He was declared dead at the scene. The matter is still under investigation.” THE MERCURY